<LP>
   LILLIAN VERNON Corp. declared a 3-for-2 stock split,
payable Aug. 14 to shareholders of record on July 30. The
Mount Vernon, N.Y., specialty-catalog retailer, which has 6.2
million common shares outstanding, said the split reflects
the company's continuing growth and will improve the
liquidity of its stock. After the split, it will have about
9.3 million common shares. In trading on the American Stock
Exchange, Lillian Vernon closed at $24.25, up 12.5 cents.
